title: Two County Tallies in Nevada Show Democratic Route to Senate
description: The path became clearer on Wednesday night as the first post-election vote tallies in Nevada and Arizona showed Democrats faring well among mail voters.
dc:creator: Nate Cohn
media:credit: Mikayla Whitmore for The New York Times
media:description: Senator Catherine Cortez Masto of Nevada carried the first round of mail ballots in Clark County and Washoe County by two to one.
